<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="683" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">McCormick</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-07"><hi rend="italic">February 7,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay instructs Mr. McCormick to ascertain, in accordance with the
                            request of the Japanese Government, whether it will be agreeable to the
                            Russian Government if the American representatives in Russia look after
                            the interests of Japan upon the withdrawal of her diplomatic and
                            consular officers.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>